# AI Assistant Extension - Environment Configuration

## Extension Environment Variables

### Development
```bash
# Use local connector API
VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
```

### Production (Vercel Deployed)
```bash
# Your Vercel-hosted connector API URL
# Replace with your actual Vercel domain after deployment
VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=https://your-project-name.vercel.app
```

### Build Targets
```bash
# Chromium (Chrome, Brave, Edge)
TARGET=chromium

# Firefox
TARGET=firefox
```

## Connector API Environment Variables

### Development
```bash
# .env file (copy from connector-api/.env.example)
PORT=3001
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-key-change-this-in-production
NODE_ENV=development
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=chrome-extension://*,moz-extension://*
```

### Production (Vercel)
Set these in Vercel dashboard:
- `NODE_ENV`: production
- `JWT_SECRET`: Strong random key (required!)
- `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`: Extension IDs after publishing

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Local Development

```bash
# Install all dependencies
npm run setup

# Terminal 1: Extension dev
npm run dev

# Terminal 2: Connector API dev
npm run dev:api

# All in one terminal (requires concurrently)
npm run dev:all
```

### 2. Build Everything

```bash
# Full build and validation
npm run validate:all

# Or individual commands
npm run typecheck:all
npm run lint:all
npm run test:all
npm run build:all
```

### 3. Deploy Connector API to Vercel

1. Push this repository to GitHub
2. Go to https://vercel.com and sign in
3. Click "New Project"
4. Select this GitHub repository
5. In "Environment Variables", add:
   - `JWT_SECRET`: Generate strong secret (e.g., `openssl rand -base64 32`)
   - `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`: `chrome-extension://*,moz-extension://*` (for development)
6. Deploy
7. Copy your Vercel URL (e.g., `https://your-project-name.vercel.app`)

### 4. Configure Extension for Vercel API

1. Create `.env` file in root:
```bash
VITE_CONNECTOR_API_URL=https://your-project-name.vercel.app
```

2. Build extension:
```bash
npm run build:chromium
npm run build:firefox
```

3. Extension will now use your Vercel-hosted connector API

## Verification

### Health Check Local API
```bash
curl http://localhost:3001/health
# Response: { "status": "ok", "version": "1.0.0", "timestamp": "..." }
```

### Health Check Vercel API
```bash
curl https://your-project-name.vercel.app/health
# Response: { "status": "ok", "version": "1.0.0", "timestamp": "..." }
```

### Test Token Exchange
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/auth/token \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "extensionId": "test-ext-123",
    "providerId": "gemini",
    "credentials": {"apiKey": "your-test-key"}
  }'
```
